#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:1
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:250
#, no-wrap
msgid "Principles of GBIF-mediated data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:6
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:254
msgid ""
"In this section, you will learn about the principles that GBIF follows with "
"regards to data and how data in the GBIF portal are FAIR."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:10
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:255
#, no-wrap
msgid "Digital object identifiers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:14
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:259
msgid ""
"A Digital Object Identifier, or DOI, is a http://www.iso.org/iso/"
"catalogue_detail?csnumber=43506[standard^], permanent identifier that "
"provides an actionable, interoperable, persistent link to any entity.  The "
"concept is that DOI differs from commonly used references like URL web links "
"because it identifies an object itself as a first-class entity, not simply "
"the place where the object is currently located."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:16
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:261
msgid ""
"In the context of GBIF.org, DOIs serve as stable identifiers for four "
"different types of things:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:18
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:263
msgid "datasets from the GBIF network"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:19
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:264
msgid "data downloads from GBIF.org"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:20
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:265
msgid ""
"research articles and reports published by scientific journals, agencies and "
"NGOs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:21
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:266
msgid "materials deposited in a general-use repository"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:28
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:273
msgid ""
"GBIF started issuing DOIs on 3 February 2015.  Downloads requested before "
"this date do not have DOIs, however, if you wish to cite older downloads, "
"you can contact helpdesk@gbif.org and we will assign DOIs as appropriate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:29
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "Standards"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:32
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:277
msgid ""
"The data available through GBIF.org and its associated services is the "
"result of the GBIF network of Participants and publishers applying shared "
"rules and conventions to describe, record and structure thousands of "
"different datasets drawn from hundreds of institutions around the world. "
"Common standards are the main enabler for bringing together the hundreds of "
"millions of primary biodiversity records in the GBIF index."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:34
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:279
msgid ""
"Within the biodiversity domain, the group most often responsible for "
"developing and maintaining data standards is http://www.tdwg.org/"
"[Biodiversity Information Standards^]. This nonprofit scientific and "
"educational association focuses on the development of standards for the "
"exchange of biological and biodiversity data. Members of the biodiversity "
"community generally refer to this group as TDWG (pronounced tad-wig)—a "
"vestigial reminder of its earlier manifestation as the Taxonomic Databases "
"Working Group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:39
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:284
msgid ""
"Darwin Core: The https://dwc.tdwg.org/[Darwin Core Standard^] (DwC) offers a "
"stable, straightforward and flexible framework for compiling biodiversity "
"data from varied and variable sources.  The majority of the datasets shared "
"through GBIF.org are published using the Darwin Core Archive format (DwC-A)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:42
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:287
msgid ""
"Ecological Metadata Language (EML): https://eml.ecoinformatics.org/"
"[Ecological Metadata Language^] is a metadata standard that records "
"information about ecological datasets in a series of modular and extensible "
"XML document types.  All of the descriptions of datasets in GBIF.org rely on "
"‘metadata’—that is, the information about data—using the open-source EML "
"standard, which is administered and maintained by https://knb.ecoinformatics."
"org/[The Knowledge Network for Biocomplexity^].  Each Darwin Core Archive "
"includes as one of its components an EML file (written in XML format)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:43
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:288
msgid ""
"BioCASe/ABCD: The http://www.biocase.org/[Biological Collection Access "
"Service^], commonly referred to as BioCASe, is an international network "
"linking biological collections data from natural history museums, botanical/"
"zoological gardens and research institutions. The http://www.biocase.org/"
"products/protocols[BioCASe protocol^] relies on the http://www.tdwg.org/"
"standards/115[Access to Biological Collections Data^] (ABCD) data exchange "
"standard, which TDWG also administers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:44
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:289
#, no-wrap
msgid "Open data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:47
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:292
msgid ""
"In keeping with a 2014 https://www.gbif.org/news/82363/new-approaches-to-"
"data-licensing-and-endorsement[decision by the GBIF governing board^], data "
"publishers must assign one of the three Creative Commons options to any "
"occurrence dataset. The Governing Board recognized the need for much greater "
"clarity both for data publishers and users on how data may be used when "
"shared via GBIF.org. https://creativecommons.org/[Creative Commons] is a "
"nonprofit organization that helps overcome legal obstacles to the sharing of "
"knowledge and creativity to address the world’s pressing challenges."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:49
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:294
msgid ""
"http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0[CC0^] - no conditions for "
"use"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:50
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:295
msgid ""
"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/[CC-BY^] - use with attribution"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:51
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:296
msgid ""
"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/[CC-BY-NC^] - non-commercial "
"use with attribution"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:54
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "FAIR data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:61
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:306
msgid ""
"Many articles from 2011-2016 documented a crisis in scientific "
"reproducibility (see below).  In 2016, the https://www.nature.com/articles/"
"sdata201618[FAIR Guiding Principles for scientific data management and "
"stewardship^] were published in https://www.nature.com/sdata/[Scientific "
"Data^].  The principles were designed to improve the Findability, "
"Accessibility, the Interoperability and the Reusability of datasets and "
"address \"an urgent need to improve the infrastructure supporting the reuse "
"of scholarly data.\" Implementation of these principles began in 2018.  You "
"can read more about http://www.go-fair.org/how-to-go-fair/[How to GO FAIR^] "
"on https://www.go-fair.org/[GO-FAIR.org^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:67
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:312
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Data found on GBIF.org are FAIR.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:70
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "*FINDABLE*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:72
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:317
msgid ""
"GBIF has https://www.gbif.org/data-quality-requirements[requirements] for "
"metadata and datasets. All datasets are identified by https://www.gbif.org/"
"faq?question=how-and-when-does-gbif-assign-digital-object-identifiers-"
"dois[Digital Object Identifiers^] (DOIs)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:76
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:321
#, no-wrap
msgid "*ACCESSIBLE*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:82
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:327
#, no-wrap
msgid "*INTEROPERABLE*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:84
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:329
msgid ""
"GBIF recommends using the https://eml.ecoinformatics.org/[Ecological "
"Metadata Language^] (EML) for datasets and https://dwc.tdwg.org/[Darwin "
"Core^] for occurrence data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:88
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:333
#, no-wrap
msgid "*REUSABLE*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data-principles.adoc:90
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:335
msgid ""
"GBIF require creative common data licenses (https://creativecommons.org/"
"publicdomain/zero/1.0[CC0^], https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0[CC "
"BY^], or https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0[CC BY-NC^]). "
"Provenance available from the GBIF portal."
msgstr ""

