#, no-wrap
msgid "Presentation transcript"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "GBIF-mediated data "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:5
msgid ""
"In this module, you will learn about primary biodiversity data and the "
"principles that GBIF follows with regards to data. You will learn how GBIF "
"makes primary biodiversity data accessible, the accepted dataset types and "
"how GBIF uses the taxonomic backbone to provide taxonomic information. You "
"will also have a chance to review the various metrics that are available for "
"the data within the portal."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Primary biodiversity data"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:11
msgid ""
"In this video (12:03), Cecilie Svenningsen, GBIF Data Product Manager, "
"shares how data is shared with GBIF and how that data might be used, along "
"with describing biodiversity standards and GBIF dataset types."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:13
msgid ""
"If you are unable to watch the embedded Vimeo video, you can xref:"
"attachment$how_data_is_shared_with_gbif._v1_1080p.mp4[download] it locally "
"(MP4 - 73.1 MB)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide1.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 1 - How is data shared on GBIF.org?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:35
msgid ""
"One thing to be mindful of is that data publishers on GBIF own and maintain "
"their data, and then they share that with GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide2.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 2 - Data publishing*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:41
msgid ""
"So the way it works is that we have a data set that is owned by an "
"organization. That organization needs to be endorsed by a GBIF node, that "
"could be a country node or any sort of participant node, to be able to share "
"data with GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:43
msgid ""
"That data then needs to be hosted somewhere in an installation, for example, "
"the integrated publishing toolkit provided by GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:45
msgid ""
"So the data sets are hosted there, and then they can be published to GBIF "
"and shared with you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:46
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide3.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 3 - Data shared on GBIF is heterogeneous*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:51
msgid ""
"Another thing to be mindful of is that data on GBIF is quite heterogeneous. "
"These organizations that share data with GBIF come from quite various "
"sources, and it's a community-endorsed process, as I had mentioned, where we "
"have the nodes endorsing the publishing organizations, and that they can be "
"anything from universities, museums, governmental agencies, et cetera."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:53
msgid ""
"So what they share can come from research projects or monitoring efforts, "
"citizen science data or collections."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:55
msgid "That is also something to be mindful of, that data is not live on GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:57
msgid ""
"You can have data that is a part of a mobilized effort of a collection, "
"museum collection that might be digitizing their data from 50 years ago, 70 "
"years ago, and the next day, it's available on GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide4.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 4 - Accessing and downloading data*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:63
msgid ""
"So just to show you how such an aggregated search can look for you as a "
"user, if you go and you want to look at a species, in this case, I'm showing "
"you the orange tip butterfly. So if you, as most of our users, go into our "
"portal and search for the species, the first thing you would encounter is "
"the species page."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:65
msgid ""
"That will show you an overall description of the species and the GBIF "
"occurrence distribution. But you would usually go to the occurrence record "
"page, where you would apply further filters."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:67
msgid ""
"In this case, I'm saying I only want records that are from 2020 to 2022, I "
"think. And I also say that it has to be in the continent of Europe."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:69
msgid ""
"So I've narrowed down my search and I click download, where I have to choose "
"different options. In this case, I'm choosing the simple option."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:71
msgid ""
"But you can also see other information, such as known issues for the data, "
"which might be something you should look into if you want to apply further "
"filters for your download, if you don't want that data included."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:73
msgid ""
"So in your GBIF user profile, you can see all the downloads you ever created."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:75
msgid ""
"In this case, I'm showing you the one I just created, the filters. But you "
"will also see that 927 data sets contributed to this aggregated search."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:77
msgid ""
"So quite a varied source contributed with data. This matters because that "
"has an impact of what will actually be in the data you download."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide5.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 5 - Reviewing a download*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:83
msgid ""
"So this is an example of that simple download I just created, where in the "
"simple download, you have less fields available, less columns. But if you "
"did the full Darwin Core archive download, you would have many fields to "
"search from. But you will notice that there's some of these fields that "
"appear to be empty, where we don't have any values. But as you can see, as "
"I'm showing you now, you do actually do have some locality information "
"shared by some publishers."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:85
msgid ""
"So that means that some publishers might be sharing data while others don't. "
"And that can matter for your analysis."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:87
msgid ""
"So for example, individual count, which can give you an idea about the "
"abundance of the species, might not necessarily be filled out by some "
"publishers, but is filled out by others."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:89
msgid ""
"And as I mentioned, if you have the full Darwin Core archive download, where "
"you have many more columns, you will see a much more patchy data set, which "
"matters for how you post-process your data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:90
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide6.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 6 - To which extent is there content in the fields you download?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:95
msgid ""
"If we go to a little more into detail of which content you can expect from "
"the data you download on GBIF, I just give you some general ideas of some of "
"the fields that you could download."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:97
msgid ""
"The GBIF ID, which we apply to the record that is shared with GBIF, is "
"always 100%. You always get all the GBIF IDs for your data. But if you are "
"looking for habitat information, if you look across all occurrence records "
"on GBIF, only around 7% have data in that field."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:99
msgid ""
"Individual counts have quite high numbers, as well as state and province, "
"but be mindful that this is because of birds. The biggest group of data we "
"have on GBIF is coming from birds, so they really up how much data we "
"actually have available. So it can be quite group specific."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:101
msgid ""
"So if you're looking for insects, you might find that the percentage of "
"values that are actually covered is quite low."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:103
msgid "With scientific name, it's pretty good."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:105
msgid ""
"For the depth, if you're looking into marine occurrences, very few "
"publishers actually share that data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:107
msgid "The same for elevation, and life stage is only 9%."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:109
msgid ""
"Most of our publishers do provide some sort of temporal data, but that could "
"be just in the form of year."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:111
msgid "So just be mindful of that when you use your data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide7.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 7 - Data standards*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:117
msgid ""
"So I'm going to talk a bit about the data standards that are behind what you "
"see on GBIF. As you noticed, the columns have quite specific names. These "
"names and fields are defined by data standards, which are maintained by a "
"global biodiversity community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide8.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 8 - Darwin Core Archive (DwC-A)*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:123
msgid ""
"So most of the data shared with GBIF is usually within a Darwin Core "
"archive, as I also mentioned earlier. And the publishers sharing data with "
"GBIF have to map their data to this Darwin Core standard."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:125
msgid ""
"It's maintained by the Biodiversity Information Standards, also called TDWG."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:127
msgid ""
"And those data standards define the field name, as I mentioned, and they "
"also sometimes define the value content that could be like a controlled "
"vocabulary or some sort of normalized value that people should use when they "
"share their data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:129
msgid ""
"So let's say you're a publisher, you're completely new to data standards and "
"publishing on GBIF. You might have a spreadsheet saying that you have a "
"name, you have a count of how many of that species you saw, and some general "
"notes about what you found."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:131
msgid ""
"Those fields have to be called scientific name for the name, for example, "
"individual count for the counts, and for the notes, you might want to put "
"those in occurrence remarks or event remarks."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:133
msgid ""
"The point is that you have specific fields to capture specific information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide9.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 9 - Available fields*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:139
msgid ""
"Now, the fields available for sharing on GBIF, it's dependent on the dataset "
"class."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:141
msgid ""
"As I mentioned, you have occurrence records. Those occurrence records is one "
"type of dataset class on GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:143
msgid ""
"So the most simple one is the metadata-only dataset, which doesn't really "
"have any data. It's just a description of the dataset. So that could be a "
"description of a collection or description of a field study, but where you "
"haven't been able to digitize the data just yet."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:145
msgid ""
"Then we also have checklist datasets, which is a list of taxon names. There "
"could be more information included, but generally, it's sharing scientific "
"names of a given area or within a different specific scope."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:147
msgid ""
"And then you have occurrences, which I mentioned before, which is the "
"evidence of a species present or a taxon present at a given date and place."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:149
msgid ""
"Now, the last type of dataset class we have is the sampling events, which "
"has a little more information because usually people have to share sampling "
"effort and protocol, and it can allow users to assess community composition "
"and abundance of species."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:150
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide10.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 10 - Dataset cores*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:155
msgid ""
"Now, those dataset classes are core tables. So if you have a dataset table "
"that is either a taxon, occurrence, or event table those tables have a "
"specific set of fields you can share. But you might want to share even more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:157
msgid ""
"For example, if you have an event dataset, you might want to share "
"individual occurrences."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:159
msgid ""
"You did a BioBlitz from start of Saturday to the end of Saturday, but at "
"that range, you found that butterfly or that beetle at a specific time "
"during that."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:161
msgid "That's an occurrence within the event of the BioBlitz."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:163
msgid ""
"Or you might have media associated. You took pictures of the different "
"insects you found during that time, or you might even have taken samples for "
"DNA, and then you have identifications based on DNA."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:165
msgid ""
"And you might have a taxon core or a checklist, as I mentioned, where you "
"have the distribution of the species covered."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide11.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:169
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 11 - Missing fields?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:171
msgid ""
"Now, we have a lot of fields available on GBIF in which you can filter down "
"and narrow your search for. But in some cases, you might not find the fields "
"that you need for your analysis."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:173
msgid ""
"If you would ever need such a field, the correct way of getting, well, at "
"least starting the discussion of getting that field into GBIF would to be to "
"go through TDWG and the Darwin Core standard."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:175
msgid ""
"You can propose new terms and changes to Darwin Core, but you have to be "
"mindful that changing data standards is a community-driven process which "
"requires a lot of engagement and patience because you need to discuss it "
"with your peers, and you need to find a common ground for adding those data. "
"So you have to consider whether the term already exists but would require an "
"update, where the new term would best be placed. Is it taxon specific? Is it "
"occurrence specific or event specific? Is it something to do with locations?"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:177
msgid ""
"And you also have to think about whether the term is better suited in an "
"extension or in one of the core tables."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:179
msgid ""
"So many people are maybe not that aware of extensions to these core tables, "
"but there's a lot of extensions out there to serve the community who wants "
"to share data or use data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:181
msgid ""
"So please familiarize yourself with them before you propose or change terms."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::how-data-is-shared_Slide12.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 12 - Dataset metadata*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:187
msgid ""
"One last thing I have to mention about the data standards is that you also "
"have a data standard called EML or Ecological Metadata Language publishers "
"use to share information about the dataset resource in which they have all "
"their data. So that is, for example, who was the people who was involved in "
"maintaining, gathering the data, the overall spatial and temporal scope of "
"the dataset, the taxonomic scope of the dataset, and any funding and project-"
"specific information, as well as methods and design."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:189
msgid ""
"So that's another standard which is not part of the TDWG standard you might "
"want to look into as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "GBIF dataset classes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:196
msgid ""
"More information on https://www.gbif.org/dataset-classes[dataset classes^] "
"can be found on the GBIF website."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:198
msgid ""
"You might also want to explore https://data-blog.gbif.org/post/choose-"
"dataset-type/[how to choose a dataset type^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "Taxonomy interpretation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:202
msgid ""
"To facilitate searching and metric generation, all occurrence records are "
"matched to two taxonomies:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:204
msgid ""
"https://www.gbif.org/dataset/7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b[Catalogue "
"of Life eXtended Release^] (COL XR) - This is the primary taxonomy used by "
"GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:206
msgid ""
"https://www.gbif.org/dataset/d7dddbf4-2cf0-4f39-9b2a-bb099caae36c[GBIF "
"backbone^] - This is a taxonomy that, up until recently, GBIF has been "
"building and integrating periodically. It is primarily based on an older "
"version of Catalogue of Life with additional taxa added in an automated way "
"from other taxonomic datasets. The build process has now been discontinued "
"in favour of the eXtended release of the Catalogue of Life. The GBIF "
"Backbone will no longer be updated, but will remain available for backwards "
"compatibility. All GBIF Backbone identifiers will be preserved and supported "
"in the API."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:208
msgid ""
"https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-processing/taxonomy-interpretation#api-"
"support[API support for taxonomy interpretation^] along with https://"
"techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-processing/taxonomy-interpretation#taxonomic-"
"indexes[Taxonomic indexes^] are documented in GBIF's technical documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:210
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Why does GBIF need taxonomy interpretation?* \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:212
msgid ""
"Without it, we wouldn’t be able to do any taxonomic search and it would be "
"difficult to generate consistent statistics and maps."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:216
msgid ""
"As you can imagine, not everyone uses the same classifications or names.  "
"This results in considerable variations in higher taxa and a large number of "
"synonyms.  This process aims to bring all these names together and organize "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "*How are the taxonomies generated?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:219
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::ChecklistBank-04-07-2026_01_43_PM.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:222
msgid ""
"https://www.catalogueoflife.org/[Catalogue of Life^] is a global index of "
"species, which aims to provide a comprehensive and authoritative list of the "
"world’s species. It is compiled from multiple taxonomic datasets and is "
"updated regularly. The https://www.gbif.org/dataset/7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-"
"b351-99906754a03b[eXtended Release^] (COL XR) builds on the Base Release by "
"programmatically integrating additional data sources. It integrates "
"information from over 58,000 overlapping taxonomic and nomenclatural global, "
"regional, national and management data sources (checklists) as well as "
"originating from digitised literature available in Catalogue of Life’s "
"infrastructure https://www.checklistbank.org/[ChecklistBank^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:224
msgid ""
"Note that many sequence-based occurrences have no Latin names but are named "
"using species hypotheses (UNITE: fungi) or Barcode Index Numbers (iBOL: "
"primarily animals). This is why adding these two major sources of stable "
"OTUs to the latest backbone taxonomy significantly improves GBIF’s indexing "
"functionality for sequence-based biodiversity data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:226
#, no-wrap
msgid "*How are the taxonimic status' defined?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:227
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::helianthusL.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:230
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Accepted*: A taxonomically accepted, current name\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Provisionally accepted*: Treated as accepted, but doubtful whether this is correct.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:232
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Synonym*: Names which point unambiguously at one species (not specifying whether homo- or heterotypic).Synonyms, in the CoL sense, include also orthographic variants and published misspellings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:233
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Ambiguous synonym*: Names which are ambiguous because they point at the current species and one or more others e.g. homonyms, pro-parte synonyms (in other words, names which appear more than in one place in the Catalogue).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Misapplied*: A misapplied name. Usually accompanied with an accordingTo on the synonym to indicate the source the misapplication can be found in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:235
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Bare name*: A name alone without any usage, neither a synonym nor a taxon.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:236
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRSciColl"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:239
msgid ""
"The Global Registry of Scientific Collections, or https://scientific-"
"collections.gbif.org/[GRSciColl^], is a comprehensive and community-curated "
"clearing house of information about scientific collections in the GBIF "
"registry. By providing information about physical scientific collections—"
"their content, location, contacts, associated institutions, and collection "
"codes and identifiers—GRSciColl offers a resource for a wide range of uses "
"by experts, researchers and members of broader society."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:243
msgid ""
"In this video (02:11), Marie Grosjean, GBIF Data Administrator, provides an "
"introduction to GRSciColl."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:245
msgid ""
"If you are unable to watch the embedded Vimeo video, you can xref:"
"attachment$getting_started_on_global_registry_of_scientific_collection_website_v1 "
"_1080p.mp4[download] it locally (MP4 - 13.3 MB)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:270
msgid ""
"GBIF assigns DOIs to all datasets and occurrence downloads.  When data is "
"used, following DOI https://www.gbif.org/citation-guidelines[citation "
"practice^] ensures an easy and consistent way of crediting dataset holders "
"while also allowing for reproducibility.  The DOIs will always resolve to "
"dataset or download pages, even if the underlying data is no longer "
"available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:281
msgid "Commonly use standards include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:298
msgid ""
"Note that the CC-BY-NC licence has a significant effect on the reusability "
"of data. GBIF encourages data publishers to choose the most open option they "
"can wherever possible. It is important to note that images are not subject "
"to the same licence that is applied to the dataset and may have more "
"restricted terms of use. Lastly, attribution/citation is a community norm, "
"so even if the publishers has waived conditions for use, attribution is "
"expected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:307
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::gofairlogo.svg"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::FairPrinciples2.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:323
msgid ""
"The https://www.gbif.org/developer/summary[GBIF Portal API^] provides a "
"machine readable interface (REST + JSON) and use the https://www.gbif.org/"
"ipt[Integrated Publishing Toolkit^] (IPT) as trusted data repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:361
#, no-wrap
msgid "Data metrics"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:365
msgid "In this section review the various metrics available for datasets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:367
msgid ""
"One of the many benefits of publishing data via GBIF is that, during the "
"indexing process, GBIF analyses all datasets and produces https://www.gbif."
"org/analytics/global[metrics^] about them. These metrics are made available "
"in several different ways:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:369
msgid "global trends"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:370
msgid "country pages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:371
msgid "dataset content statistics"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:372
msgid "dataset download activity"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:374
msgid ""
"Participants and publishers can use this information to improve the quality "
"of their datasets, e.g. by addressing issues detected during the indexing "
"process. They can also use the access statistics as evidence of real user "
"interest in their datasets and potential use of the published data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:376
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Global data trends*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:378
msgid ""
"GBIF.org regularly updates analytics to provide an overview of global trends "
"in the data from 2008 to the present. The charts illustrate trends in:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:380
msgid "occurrence records"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:381
msgid "species counts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:382
msgid "time and seasonality"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:383
msgid "completeness and precision"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:384
msgid "geographic coverage for recorded species"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:385
msgid "data sharing with country of origin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:386
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::10_trends.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:389
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Dataset content statistics*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/gbif-mediated-data.adoc:391
